Package: NilpotentMinimum
Type: Package
Title: Basic R Functionality for (Strong and Weak) Nilpotent Minimum fuzzy logics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Igor", "Yegin",
      email = "igor.yegin@stir.ac.uk",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: (Strong) Nilpotent Minimum (commonly shortened to NM) is a class of t-norms 
    introduced by Fodor (1995) and later generalised for weak negation by 
    Esteva and Godo (2001). NM t-norm is an archetypical example of a non-continuous 
    t-norm which has a well-defined residuum and a symmetric induced negation with a 
    unique fixpoint. This package provides a number of R functions for NM logic 
    whose syntax is mostly identical to that of lfl package, 
    except NilpotentMininum is written entirely in native R code.
